Format: https://www.debian.org/doc/packaging-manuals/copyright-format/1.0/
Upstream-Name: supersonic
Upstream-Contact: Sam Aaron <sam@sonic-pi.net>
Source: https://github.com/samaaron/supersonic
Files-Excluded: external_libs/ASIOSDK2.3.4
Comment: The Steinberg ASIO SDK (Windows-only; dual-licensed proprietary or
 GPL-3) is excluded from the Debian source tarball because the directory also
 carries non-free documentation PDFs and trademark-encumbered logo artwork.
 It is not used on Linux.
 .
 The source package is assembled from three upstream tarballs:
 the main tarball (this repository), the "link" component (pristine Ableton
 Link 4.0 with its asio-standalone submodule; upstream patches under
 debian/patches apply to it), and the "rust-vendor" component (the output of
 `cargo vendor` for the committed rust/Cargo.lock). See debian/README.source.

Files: *
Copyright: 2025-2026 Sam Aaron <sam@sonic-pi.net>
License: GPL-3+

Files: js/*
 rust/*
 src/nif/supersonic.erl
 test/freestanding/freestanding_main.cpp
 esp32s3/main/main.cpp
Copyright: 2025-2026 Sam Aaron <sam@sonic-pi.net>
License: Expat or GPL-3+
Comment: The client libraries are dual-licensed so non-GPL hosts can embed
 them; the audio engine itself (src/) is GPL-3+ only.

Files: js/workers/scsynth_audio_worklet.js
Copyright: 2025-2026 Sam Aaron <sam@sonic-pi.net>
License: GPL-3+
Comment: The AudioWorklet that executes the GPL engine WASM is not part of
 the dual-licensed client-library set (see its SPDX header).

Files: src/synth/*
Copyright: 2002-2023 James McCartney and SuperCollider contributors
License: GPL-2+
Comment: SuperSonic's audio engine is a heavily modified fork of
 SuperCollider's scsynth server. Combined with the GPL-3+ first-party code
 the effective licence of the built binary is GPL-3+.

Files: src/synth/external_libraries/boost/*
Copyright: 1998-2024 Boost contributors
License: BSL-1.0
Comment: bcp-extracted header subset of Boost 1.86, unused when built with
 -DSUPERSONIC_SYSTEM_BOOST=ON (as this package does).

Files: src/synth/external_libraries/nova-simd/*
Copyright: 2008-2012 Tim Blechmann
License: GPL-2+

Files: src/synth/external_libraries/TLSF-2.4.6/*
Copyright: 2005-2008 Miguel Masmano Tello
License: GPL-2 or LGPL-2.1
Comment: The TLSF real-time allocator is dual-licensed; this package uses it
 under the GPL-2 option, compatible with the engine's GPL licence.

Files: src/synth/common/fftlib.c
Copyright: 1995-1996 John Green (Naval Undersea Warfare Center, USA)
License: public-domain
 This FFT implementation was written by John Green, an employee of the US
 federal government (NUWC, New London), and carries no licence statement.
 Works of US federal government employees produced in the course of their
 duties are not subject to domestic copyright protection (17 U.S.C. 105).
 The same file ships in Debian's existing supercollider package.

Files: src/vendor/oscpack/*
Copyright: 2004-2013 Ross Bencina <rossb@audiomulch.com>
License: Expat
Comment: The licence text includes non-binding requests regarding use.

Files: external/midir/*
Copyright: 2015-2024 Patrick Reisert and RtMidi contributors
License: Expat
Comment: Vendored fork of the midir Rust crate (0.11.0) carrying local
 patches (timestamped send for WebMIDI/CoreMIDI). Consumed as a cargo path
 dependency; not replaceable by a crates.io copy without losing the patches.

Files: external_libs/erlang_headers/*
Copyright: 2009-2025 Ericsson AB
License: Apache-2.0
Comment: Bundled Erlang/OTP NIF headers, used only when the BEAM NIF is
 built (-DBUILD_NIF=ON). This package does not build the NIF.

Files: packages/supersonic-scsynth-samples/*
Copyright: none (dedicated to the public domain by their authors)
License: CC0-1.0
Comment: Per-sample provenance (freesound.org links and donations) is
 recorded in packages/supersonic-scsynth-samples/PROVENANCE.md. Retained in
 the source package because the test suite exercises sample loading; not
 shipped in the binary package.

Files: packages/supersonic-scsynth-synthdefs/*
Copyright: 2013-2026 Sam Aaron and Sonic Pi contributors
License: Expat
Comment: Compiled SuperCollider synth definitions (.scsyndef). The preferred
 form of modification — the sclang synthdef designs they are compiled from —
 is maintained in the Sonic Pi repository:
 https://github.com/sonic-pi-net/sonic-pi (etc/synthdefs/designs). Retained
 in the source package because the test suite loads them; not shipped in the
 binary package.

Files: link/*
Copyright: 2016-2024 Ableton AG
License: GPL-2+
Comment: Pristine Ableton Link 4.0 ("link" component tarball). Debian ships
 ableton-link-dev 3.x, which is too old for this package and lacks the four
 upstream-carried patches applied under debian/patches (loopback-only
 discovery, peer enumeration, monotonic commit timestamps, a LinkAudio
 teardown race fix).

Files: link/modules/asio-standalone/*
Copyright: 2003-2024 Christopher M. Kohlhoff
License: BSL-1.0

Files: rust-vendor/*
Copyright: various Rust crate authors; see the LICENSE files inside each
 crate directory and rust/Cargo.lock for the exact crate set
License: Expat or Apache-2.0
Comment: Output of `cargo vendor` for the committed rust/Cargo.lock. The
 licence allow-list is machine-enforced by upstream's rust/deny.toml (MIT,
 Apache-2.0 with or without LLVM-exception, BSD-2-Clause, BSD-3-Clause, ISC,
 Zlib, Unicode-3.0, Unicode-DFS-2016, CC0-1.0, MPL-2.0); every vendored
 crate is available under at least one of Expat or Apache-2.0 except a small
 number under the other listed permissive licences — each crate directory
 carries its own licence text.

